# Copy to vault/github.env (create vault/ if needed). File is gitignored.
#
# GitHub does not let anyone re-download an existing token. If you lost it,
# revoke the old one at GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → Tokens, then create a new PAT.
#
# Classic PAT: https://github.com/settings/tokens — scopes e.g. repo (private repos), read:org if needed.
# Fine-grained: https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens — pick repos + permissions.
#
# For git over HTTPS, many tools use:
#   git config credential.helper osxkeychain   # macOS
#   # then use https://github.com and username + PAT as password when prompted
#
# SSH (alternative to HTTPS + token): generate a key, add the *public* key at
#   https://github.com/settings/keys
# Then use remote URL git@github.com:OWNER/REPO.git

GITHUB_TOKEN=
# Optional — some CLIs use this
# GITHUB_USERNAME=
